Date: 0/0/1955
Source: Wool Away!
Author: BOWEN
Vol / Page: 92
Edition:
Quote: In skirting a fleece use two hands - holding the edge of the fleece in one hand, take off the skirt with the other. If skirtings are pulled off without one hand holding good wool, a lot of this good wool tears out of the fleece and goes in with the skirtings.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1973
Source: Tussock Fever
Author: FERNANDEZ
Vol / Page: 166
Edition:
Quote: `What's 2nd Pcs H?' `Grade 2, pieces - that's skirtings - hogget wool.' `And Bls E?' `That's belly wool. E grade bellies.' `Lox?' `Oh, that's floor sweepings.' `What about Lbs Wigs?' `Lamb top-knots - off the head.'
Notes:

