Notes:

Date: 0/0/1985
Source: Woolscours of NZ
Author: BREMNER
Vol / Page: 10
Edition:
Quote: <i>Skirtings </i> wool removed form edges of fleece, below average quality of bulk of fleece, of inferior commercial value - short stapled pieces, sweated locks, stained wool etc. <i>Ibid.</i> 17 ... colonial woolscourers who removed grease, sticks and thistles from the locks and pieces - the dirty, inferior quality skirtings trimmed from the fleeces.
